======
 M210
======

Author: Tuomas Räsänen (tuos) <tuos@codegrove.org>
Homepage: http://codegrove.org/projects/m210
License: GPLv3+ (see COPYING for details)
Version: 0.4

Description
===========

M210 is a software project which aims to provide easy-to-use tools for
controlling and using `Pegasus Tablet Mobile Notetaker M210`_ in modern
Linux desktop environments.

.. _Pegasus Tablet Mobile Notetaker M210: http://www.pegatech.com/?CategoryID=207&ArticleID=268

Build requirements
==================

- Python 2.6.x.
- Development files for Python.

Runtime requirements
====================

- Python bindings for DBus.
- PyQt4.
- Upstart.

Downloading
===========

- Ubuntu package: https://launchpad.net/~tuos/+archive/codegrove
- Tarball: http://launchpad.net/m210/trunk/0.4/+download/m210-0.4.tar.gz
- Development: http://code.launchpad.net/m210 ::

    bzr clone lp:m210

Installing
==========

Ubuntu
------

Add `Codegrove PPA`_ to your system and install using standard
tools. For example with apt-get::

  sudo apt-get install m210

.. _Codegrove PPA: https://launchpad.net/~tuos/+archive/codegrove

Other systems
-------------

Satisfy the requirements listed above and then build and install
normally::

  ./configure
  make && make install

Bug reporting
=============

Please report bugs at http://bugs.launchpad.net/m210 .
